-- Goals in Afghanistan Can Be Met by 2014, Australia's Defence Minister Says
-- B y   M a r i o n   R a e
-- 2010-10-18T20:56:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-18/australia-s-goals-in-afghanistan-can-be-met-by-2014-defence-minister-says.html
Australia’s military commitment in
Afghanistan can achieve the goal of putting that nation’s
security forces in the position of managing their own affairs by
2014, Defence Minister Stephen Smith told Australian
Broadcasting Corp. radio today. Smith wouldn’t commit to a date
for troops to leave the country.  To contact the reporter on this story:
